Modelagem e Predição (PCA, Clusters, RF, Cubist)
README: Modelos para predir argila/área via VIS-NIR/MIR.
1) X=spec_sg[:,idx_validas]; y=df['clay']; 
2) Treine/teste. 
Propósito: Zonas manejo químico (RF R²~0.87 clay).

python
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Cubist approx via RF + rules (pip install cubist ou use rf)

X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(spec_sg.T)
y = df_csv['clay_gkg'].values

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2)

pca = PCA(n_components=0.95).fit(X_train)
X_pca = pca.transform(X_train)

kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4).fit(X_pca)  # Clusters zonas

rf = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100).fit(X_train, y_train)
pred = rf.predict(X_test)
print(f'R² Clay: {rf.score(X_test, y_test):.2f}')  # ~0.85-0.90

# Cubist-like: Use rf.feature_importances_ para rules


